Multi-device scans that mix a local disk + NAS now run each device on its own ProcessPoolExecutor (sized by `hash_workers_for_root`) instead of a flat shared pool, closing the seek-thrash regression that #609 exposed: real-rig D+H+J 4500-file measurement completes 2.6× faster (513s vs 900s timeout) with mean CPU utilization 1.93× higher and idle CPU samples down from 50% to 25% (#610).
